==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matweed
<hw>Mat"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name of several maritime grasses, as the sea sand-reed (<spn>Ammophila
arundinacea</spn>) which is used in Holland to bind the sand of the
seacoast dikes (see <cref>Beach grass</cref>, under <er>Beach</er>);
also, the <spn>Lygeum Spartum</spn>, a Mediterranean grass of similar
habit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maty</ent>⟦br⟧
